at this dry cleaners.

164
00:11:04,307 --> 00:11:07,901
He is dead while he's shoplifting.
We are watching him dead.

165
00:11:08,008 --> 00:11:11,000
- Dead man walking.
- Dead man shopping.

166
00:11:11,106 --> 00:11:14,403
We think that he took Jim's ring.

167
00:11:14,508 --> 00:11:16,400
- What do you know about voodoo?
- I don't know.

168
00:11:16,508 --> 00:11:19,502
- What I've seen in horror movies?
- That's unfortunate, but it's typical.

169
00:11:19,605 --> 00:11:20,901
It's all right.

170
00:11:21,006 --> 00:11:23,503
The voodoo culture is very,
very rich in history.

171
00:11:23,606 --> 00:11:25,902
They believe in something
called tri-bon-age.

172
00:11:26,007 --> 00:11:27,801
Which roughly translates to
"earth soul".

173
00:11:27,906 --> 00:11:31,802
The haitians believe that when you die,
your earth soul is released to the cosmos,

174
00:11:31,907 --> 00:11:35,102
but sometimes your earth soul gets
stuck. Maybe it even comes back

175
00:11:35,206 --> 00:11:37,303
and gets put into a corpse.

176
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:39,100
- Ever heard of zombies?
- Yeah.

177
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:40,701
Yeah, probably what you've
seen in the movies.

178
00:11:40,805 --> 00:11:43,300
Well, the myth starts, somebody,
usually a voodoo priest

179
00:11:43,408 --> 00:11:45,902
can take that earth soul, put it
into a corpse, and control it,

180
00:11:46,007 --> 00:11:49,002
make it do whatever it wants.
Walk, talk, whatever.

181
00:11:49,106 --> 00:11:52,102
But sometimes the earth soul...
not very happy about it.

182
00:11:52,206 --> 00:11:53,203
And that's why it's coming to me.

183
00:11:53,308 --> 00:11:54,702
Did you see how clumsy
it was in that video?

184
00:11:54,808 --> 00:11:56,301
Yeah, like he couldn't
stand on its feet.

185
00:11:56,405 --> 00:11:58,603
Yeah, it's like the soul is trying
restore control over the body.

186
00:11:58,708 --> 00:12:00,403
They're literally at war
with each other, Melinda

187
